<HEAD>Snow In The East; Rain In The West</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Snow fell this morning in New York, Michigan and parts of the
West and Midwest, and golf ball-sized hail was reported overnight in
Alabama.
   The snow was reported in northern and western New York, lower
Michigan, eastern Minnesota, southern and western Montana, eastern
Idaho and western Wyoming.
   Evening thunderstorms on Wednesday produced golf ball-sized hail
at Marion Junction, Ala., and dime-sized hail at Sunbury, N.C.
   A winter storm warning was posted today for heavy snow and gusty
winds over northwest Montana.
   Snow advisories also were issued for north-central and northeast
California as well as across the southern Sierra Nevada of central
California.
   Winter storm watches were in effect over the northern Sierra
Nevada of California and higher elevations of the Tahoe Valley in
Nevada.
   Rain was reported over the Oregon coast and northwest California.
Showers and thunderstorms extended from Virginia across the western
portion of the Carolinas, northern Georgia, Alabama, Mississippi and
Louisiana.
   Today's forecast called for rain over the Pacific Northwest and
northern and central California; snow over much of Nevada, the
Sierra Nevada, northeast Minnesota and upper Michigan; and strong,
gusty winds over eastern California and western Nevada.
   High temperatures were to reach the teens and 20s in western
Montana, North Dakota, Minnesota, Wisconsin and Michigan; the 30s
and 40s in South Dakota, Nebraska, the Great Lakes and New England;
the 70s and 80s in southern California, the southern Plateau, the
southern Rockies, the southern Plains, the lower Mississippi Valley,
the Gulf Coast and the southern Atlantic Coast.
   The remainder of the nation could expect highs in the 50s and 60s.
   Temperatures around the nation at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 1 degree
below zero at Marquette, Mich., to 73 degrees at McAllen, Texas.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 55 partly cloudy; Boston 46 cloudy; Buffalo 29
snow; Charleston, S.C. 65 fair; Cincinnati 26 fair; Cleveland 31
partly cloudy; Detroit 24 fair; Miami 71 fair; New York 50 cloudy;
Philadelphia 48 cloudy; Pittsburgh 34 partly cloudy; Portland, Maine
43 cloudy; Washington 51 wind.
   _Central: Bismarck 10 fair; Chicago 27 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth 44
fair; Denver 37 fair; Des Moines 29 fair; Indianapolis 26 fair;
Kansas City 36 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 18 cloudy; Nashville 37
fair; New Orleans 65 foggy; St. Louis 34 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 41 fair; Anchorage 23 fair; Las Vegas 61 fair;
Los Angeles 55 fair; Phoenix 68 fair; Salt Lake City 42 fair; San
Diego 56 cloudy; San Francisco 53 cloudy; Seattle 43 cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 23 cloudy; Toronto 25 snow.
