<FIRST>r a PM-People-Letterman-Gumbel     03-16 0211</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-People-Letterman-Gumbel,0217</SECOND>
<HEAD>Gumbel And Letterman Reportedly Talking Again</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fresh from his ``kiss and make-up'' session with
``Today'' show weatherman Willard Scott, Bryant Gumbel has
apparently wiped another entry off his grudge slate _ David
Letterman.
   Gumbel called the host of ``Late Night with David Letterman''
recently to thank him for returning a copy of the now-famous memo
Gumbel had written criticizing some ``Today'' co-workers, including
Scott, the Daily News reported today.
   The newspaper said that whoever leaked the memo to the news media
apparently also sent a copy to Letterman, with whom Gumbel had been
feuding.
   That rift began when Letterman used a bullhorn to interrupt a
taping of the ``Today'' show in 1985 at the Rockefeller Center
skating rink. Letterman had shouted down from a building overlooking
the rink, ``I am Larry Grossman, president of NBC News ... and I'm
not wearing any pants!''
   Gumbel was reportedly furious, but according to Letterman's
executive producer, Jack Rollins, ``the two of them are back
talking.''
   Asked if Gumbel might agree to appear again on Letterman's show,
also on NBC, Rollins said, ``Anything can happen, but that's not up
to me.''
   On Monday, Scott kissed Gumbel on the cheek during the ``Today''
show as they buried their hatchet.
</TEXT>
