<FIRST>r a PM-RobberRide     03-16 0169</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Robber Ride,0173</SECOND>
<HEAD>Chattanooga Bank Robber Gets Away In Cab To Nashville</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man robbed a bank in Chattanooga and
took a $210 getaway cab ride to Nashville _ paid for with the loot _
before being arrested in a motel room, police said.
   The unidentified cabbie told police Wednesday he had no idea his
passenger, Paul Fabio Martin, had allegedly robbed a bank and said
Martin even bought him a hamburger on the 2{-hour drive, according
to police.
   Martin, 31, of Cleveland, was being held today in Nashville on
charges of armed robbery, said FBI spokesman Verne Gauby.
   The robber entered a bank Wednesday morning, fired a shot into
the air, took an undisclosed amount of cash and drove off, Gauby
said. Soon after, Chattanooga police found his car nearby and
learned he had hailed a cab.
   The cab driver was found in nearby LaVergne and said he had
dropped off the man at a Nashville motel, said Nashville police Sgt.
Dennis Birdwell.
</TEXT>
