<HEAD>Presidential Guard Runs Amok, Wounds Two</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A soldier who was part of the
contingent assigned to protect President Corazon Aquino went on a
shooting spree and wounded two people before neighbors stabbed and
beat him to death, police said Thursday.
   A police report said Patrolman Ramil Villafranca went on a
shooting rampage late Wednesday in his neighborhood in the
working-class district of Tondo and shot and wounded two people.
   Residents then pulled out knives and clubs, chased Villafranca,
then beat and stabbed the soldier, the report said. Villafranca's
attackers fled before police arrived, it said.
   The report did not say what triggered Villafranca's rage.
