<FIRST>r f PM-AmericanExpansion     03-16 0199</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-American Expansion,0207</SECOND>
<HEAD>AMR Corp. To Expand Headquarters Complex</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   F0RT WORTH (AP) _ The parent corporation of American Airlines is
constructing a 750,000-square-foot, six-story addition to the
corporate headquarters near Dallas-Fort Worth International Airport,
company officials say.
   The $95 million office building is being built by AMR Corp., the
airline's parent company, and will increase the size of AMR's
headquarters complex by about one-third.
   Donald J. Carty, American senior vice president, said the new
building is needed to meet the company's growth needs.
   ``Over the last four years, American's employment in the
Dallas-Fort Worth area has increased from about 12,400 employees to
nearly 21,400,'' Carty said.
   Airline spokesman Al Becker said some of the airline's 2,400
employees who will work in the new building will be hired during the
next year and some administrative functions now housed in other AMR
facilities will be relocated when the new building opens next March.
   ``We are reviewing that right now,'' Becker said. ``There are any
number of administrative departments we are looking at moving
there.''
   Completion of the new building will give AMR about 2.5 million
square feet of office space in six buildings at the south end of the
airport.
</TEXT>
