<FIRST>d f BC-EEC-Romania     03-16 0101</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-EEC-Romania,0105</SECOND>
<HEAD>Freeze Trade Talks With Romania</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STRASBOURG, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The European Economic Community said
Thursday it has frozen talks for a new trade accord with Romania
because of what the economic bloc regards as the country's human
rights abuses.
   EEC External Relations Commissioner Frans Andriessen said
discussions could not go on unless the government in Bucharest
betters its human rights record.
   The EEC has had a trade accord with Romania, covering only
industrial goods, since 1980. In talks for a new pact, the EEC
sought to broaden the accord by adding cooperative ventures and
trade in farm goods.
</TEXT>
