<HEAD>Predict $4 Billion Cordless Telephone Market by mid 90s</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Europeaan Economic Community
Thursday predicted the cordless telephone market in Europe could
reach from $3.5 to $4.6 billion in Europe alone by 1995.
   The economic bloc said in a study that the market would be big
enough to allow handsets to sell for as cheaply as 200-250 European
currency units, or between $222 and $227 at today's prices and sales
should be as successful as for consumer products such as video
recorders.
