``triple witching hour'' due on Friday, when the last trading occurs
in a series of stock-index options and futures.
   There was talk on the Street that this quarterly phenomenon could
produce more volatility than recent similar occasions, since the
pace of computer program trading by professionals using these
contracts appears to have revived lately.
   Gainers among the blue chips included General Electric, up \ at
46[; USX, up { at 32|, and International Business Machines, up 1[ at
