<HEAD>MacGregor Sporting Goods Inc. Files For Chapter 11 Bankruptcy</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEWARK, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   MacGregor Sporting Goods Inc. filed a
petition Thursday for reorganization under federal bankruptcy laws.
   The company, based in East Rutherford, N.J., lists $37 million in
liabilities, including $5 million owed to more than 300 unsecured
creditors, said MacGregor spokesman J. Harrison Beal.
   MacGregor has severe cash flow problems primarily because it
can't obtain adequate capital, Beal said, but declined to be more
specific.
   MacGregor is an independent maker, importer and marketer of team
sports equipment and athletic clothing in the United States.
